  <p class=3D"t-rtf-style--body3"><span style=3D"color: rgb(92,122,140);">H=
ere are five key reasons to use a strong password generator:</span></p>
<ol>
<li class=3D"t-rtf-style--body3"><span style=3D"color: rgb(92,122,140);">Ha=
ckers have <a href=3D"https://www.avast.com/c-password-cracking-techniques"=
 target=3D"_self" style=3D"border-bottom-style: dotted;">ways to crack a pa=
ssword</a> in seconds: <a href=3D"https://www.avast.com/c-what-is-a-brute-f=
orce-attack" target=3D"_self" style=3D"border-bottom-style: dotted;">Brute =
force attacks</a> allow cybercriminals to test millions of passwords rapidl=
y, particularly short passwords or ones related to common words.</span></li=
>
<li class=3D"t-rtf-style--body3"><span style=3D"color: rgb(92,122,140);">Mo=
st people create easy-to-guess passwords: People often use common words, na=
mes, or predictable patterns for passwords. This can make these kinds of pa=
sswords vulnerable to dictionary attacks.</span></li>
<li class=3D"t-rtf-style--body3"><span style=3D"color: rgb(92,122,140);">Ra=
ndomly generated passwords are much stronger: A truly randomized password w=
ith uppercase and lowercase numbers plus symbols is much harder to crack th=
an one created by a person.</span></li>
<li class=3D"t-rtf-style--body3"><a href=3D"https://www.avast.com/c-how-to-=
detect-remove-keylogger" target=3D"_self" class=3D"t-rtf-style--body3" styl=
e=3D"border-bottom-style: dotted;">Keyloggers</a><span style=3D"color: rgb(=
92,122,140);"> and malware can steal the passwords you type: The former rec=
ords everything you type, including passwords, while other kinds of malware=
 can intercept logins or steal saved credentials.</span></li>
<li class=3D"t-rtf-style--body3"><span style=3D"color: rgb(92,122,140);">We=
 suggest combining strong passwords with cybersecurity software: Strong pas=
swords provide a good start, but for more in-depth digital security, softwa=
re like our Avast Free Antivirus can offer you much greater peace of mind.<=
/span></li>
</ol>

